  "prompt": "Is T-fal cookware oven safe?",
  "response": "Yes, many T-fal cookware products are oven safe, but it depends on the specific product and its materials. Here\u2019s a general guide:\n\n1. **Nonstick Cookware**: Most T-fal nonstick pans are oven safe up to **350\u00b0F (175\u00b0C)**. However, this can vary by model, so check the manufacturer\u2019s instructions for the specific pan.\n\n2. **Stainless Steel Cookware**: T-fal stainless steel pots and pans are typically oven safe to higher temperatures, often up to **500\u00b0F (260\u00b0C)** or more. Again, check the product details for confirmation.\n\n3. **Handles and Lids**: Even if the cookware body is oven safe, the handles or lids may not be. Some handles are made of plastic or silicone, which have lower heat tolerances. Ensure all components are oven safe before use.\n\n4. **Product-Specific Information**: Always refer to the user manual or product packaging for the exact oven-safe temperature range and any limitations.\n\nIf you\u2019re unsure, avoid exposing the cookware to high oven temperatures to prevent damage.",
